  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6773.45 sitting just 0.50 points below the GEX flip at 6774, dealers are in a neutral hedging stance but will aggressively sell any push toward the massive 6780 gamma wall (+24.7B). The PIN regime with heavy positive gamma concentration from 6775-6800 creates a strong magnetic pull toward fair value, while the gex_surge event suggests dealers are rapidly adjusting hedges as flows hit the market. Key resistance at 6780/6785 should act as concrete ceiling with dealers selling into strength, while any dip toward 6755 (-5.3B negative gamma) triggers dealer buying support.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect tight range-bound action between 6755-6780 with strong rejection at the upper boundary.",
